member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.DoubleParam.MIPGapAbs

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.DoubleParam.FuncMaxVal

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.DoubleParam.TuneCleanup
member.summary: Enables a cleanup phase at the end of tuning. The parameter indicates the percentage of total tuning time to devote to this phase, with a goal of reducing the number of parameter changes required to achieve the best tuning result..

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.DoubleParam.CSQueueTimeout
member.summary: Queue timeout for new jobs.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.DoubleParam.FuncPieceLength
member.summary: Piece length for PWL translation of general function constraints without own options specified.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.DoubleParam.Heuristics

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.DoubleParam.PoolGap
member.summary: Maximum optimality gap for stored solutions (relative).

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.DoubleParam.PreSOS2BigM

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.DoubleParam.PoolGapAbs

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.DoubleParam.BestBdStop

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.DoubleParam.FuncPieceError
member.summary: Error allowed for PWL translation of general function constraints without own options specified.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.DoubleParam.FuncPieceRatio

member.summary: Feasible solution objective threshold. Optimization stops when the best feasible solution objective is at least as good as the specified value.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.DoubleParam.NodeLimit
member.summary: Limit on the number of branch-and-bound nodes that will be explored. Optimization will terminate when this limit is reached.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.DoubleParam.Cutoff

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.DoubleParam.FeasibilityTol

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.DoubleParam.MarkowitzTol
member.summary: Threshold pivoting tolerance. Used to limit numerical error in the simplex algorithm. A larger value may avoid numerical problems in rare situations, but it will harm performance for most models.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.DoubleParam.PreSOS1BigM
member.summary: Largest big-M value presolve is allowed to use when converting an SOS-1 constraint into binary form.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.DoubleParam.TimeLimit
member.summary: Limit on the amount of time that will be used for an optimization. Optimization will terminate when this limit is reached.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.DoubleParam.ImproveStartNodes
member.summary: The explored node count at which the MIP solve will switch to a strategy that gives up on moving the best bound and instead devotes all of its effort towards finding better feasible solutions.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.DoubleParam.NoRelHeurWork
member.summary: Amount of time (in seconds) used by the NoRel heuristic, which searches for feasible solutions to a MIP model before solving the root relaxation.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.DoubleParam.ImproveStartTime
member.summary: The elapsed solver runtime at which the MIP solve will switch to a strategy that gives up on moving the best bound and instead devotes all of its effort towards finding better feasible solutions.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.DoubleParam.TuneTimeLimit
member.summary: Limit on the amount of time that will be used for the tuning tool (in seconds).

member.summary: Integer feasibility tolerance. Integer variables must take values that are no more than the specified tolerance away from the nearest integer.

member.summary: Implied bound cut generation. Overrides the Cuts parameter.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.SubMIPCuts
member.summary: Sub-MIP cut generation. Overrides the Cuts parameter.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.NodeMethod
member.summary: Algorithm used to solve the MIP node relaxations.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.SiftMethod
member.summary: The method to solve sifting subproblem. By default, the algorithm chooses automatically.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.DegenMoves
member.summary: Limit on degenerate simplex moves. These moves are performed to improve the integrality of the current relaxation solution. By default, the algorithm chooses the number of moves to perform automatically.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.ZeroHalfCuts
member.summary: Zero-half cut generation. Overrides the Cuts parameter.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.MinRelNodes
member.summary: Number of nodes to explore in the Minimum Relaxation heuristic. Heuristic is performed at the end of the MIP root node, and only when no feasible solution is available.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.MIQCPMethod
member.summary: Indicator to solve QCP node relaxation or to use outer approximation.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.IntegralityFocus
member.summary: Integrality focus parameter. 1 to enable, 0 to disable.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.NumericFocus
member.summary: Numerical focus. This parameter controls the degree to which the code attempts to detect and manage numerical issues. The default setting (0) makes an automatic choice, with a slight preference for speed.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.SolutionNumber
member.summary: The current solution number. When querying an alternate MIP solution through the Xn, ObjNVal or PoolObjVal attribute, determines which solution is retrieved.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.Symmetry
member.summary: Symmetry detection level. By default, the algorithm choose automatically.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.TSPort
member.summary: Token server port.

member.summary: The number of concurrent MIP jobs. A value of 'n' causes the MIP solver to solve 'n' independent MIP models, using different parameter settings for each. The optimization terminates when the the first model solves.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.OutputFlag
member.summary: Indicates whether Gurobi output should be enabled/disabled.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.ModKCuts
member.summary: Mod-K cut generation. Overrides the Cuts parameter.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.DualReductions
member.summary: Determines whether dual reductions in MIP are used. Disable dual reductions if you plan to add lazy constraints. Otherwise, incorrect solutions may result.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.PumpPasses
member.summary: Number of passes of the MIP feasibility pump heuristic performed. Heuristic is performed at the end of the MIP root node, and only when no feasible solution is available.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.ServerTimeout
member.summary: Network timeout.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.MultiObjPre
member.summary: Initial presolve on multi-objective models.

member.summary: Format of the presolved MIQCP model.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.PreSparsify
member.summary: Presolve matrix sparsification.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.InfUnbdInfo
member.summary: Indicates whether additional information should be made available for infeasible or unbounded LP models.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.RelaxLiftCuts
member.summary: Relax-and-lift cut generation. Overrides the Cuts parameter.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.Threads
member.summary: Parallel Gurobi MIP thread count. The default value of 0 uses all of the processors in the machine.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.Aggregate
member.summary: Indicates whether aggregation is enabled or disabled in presolve. In rare instances, aggregation can lead to an accumulation of numerical errors. Turning it off can sometimes improve solution accuracy.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.Quad
member.summary: Quad precision computation in simplex. By default, the algorithm chooses automatically.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.PoolSolutions
member.summary: Number of solutions to store for a MIP model.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.Presolve

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.PartitionPlace
member.summary: Controls when the partition heuristic runs.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.JSONSolDetail
member.summary: Controls amount of information in a JSON solution string.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.Record
member.summary: Replay mode, which writes one or more files that capture the sequence of Gurobi commands that your program issues. These files can be replayed later using the Gurobi command-line tool.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.CSPriority
member.summary: Job priority for Compute Server job.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.GomoryPasses
member.summary: Maximum number of Gomory cut passes performed. Overrides the Cuts parameter.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.UpdateMode
member.summary: The way how to update a model. Value 1 is default and allows adding both new variables and new constraints before calling update, while value 0 doesn't allow. In most cases, value 0 and value 1 will have the same behavior for updating a model.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.DisplayInterval
member.summary: Frequency at which log lines are printed (in seconds).

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.BarIterLimit
member.summary: Limit on the number of barrier iterations that will be performed. Optimization will terminate when this limit is reached.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.SimplexPricing
member.summary: Simplex variable pricing strategy.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.TuneCriterion
member.summary: The tuning criterion. A MIP model can often be too hard to solve. Different users may have different criteria, some want smaller MIPGap, while others want better incumbent solutions. This parameter allows you to specify different tuning citerions, 0 for runtime, 1 for MIPGap, 2 for objective value. The default value of -1 chooses automatically.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.Seed
member.summary: Random number seed.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.TuneJobs
member.summary: The number of jobs for distributed parallel tuning. A value of 'n' causes the tuning tool to distribute tuning work among 'n' parallel jobs. Jobs are distributed among a set of distributed worker machines. Use the WorkerPool parameter to point to the Remote Services cluster that will provide the distributed workers.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.MultiObjMethod
member.summary: Warm-start method to solve for subsequent objectives.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.PoolSearchMode
member.summary: Approach used to find solutions in the MIP search.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.GUBCoverCuts
member.summary: GUB cover cut generation. Overrides the Cuts parameter.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.RINS
member.summary: Frequency at which to apply the RINS heuristic. The default value of -1 is an automatic setting. A value of 0 shuts off the RINS heuristic. Setting the parameter to a positive value 'n' applies the RINS at every n-th node in the MIP search tree.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.Method
member.summary: Algorithm used to solve continuous linear models.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.CrossoverBasis
member.summary: Type of initial crossover basis construction. The default value of 0 builds a basis quickly. Choose value 1 for a more expensive basis that is often more numerically stable.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.StartNodeLimit
member.summary: Limit on the number of branch-and-bound nodes explored when completing a partial MIP start.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.NetworkCuts
member.summary: Network cut generation. Overrides the Cuts parameter.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.TuneOutput
member.summary: The amount of output produced by the tuning tool. Level 0 produces no output; level 1 produces tuning summary output only when a new best parameter set is found; level 2 produces tuning summary output for each parameter set that is tried; level 3 produces tuning summary output, plus detailed solver output, for each parameter set tried.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.SubMIPNodes
member.summary: Limit on the number of nodes explored in local search heuristics.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.FlowPathCuts
member.summary: Flow path cut generation. Overrides the Cuts parameter.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.AggFill
member.summary: Presolve aggregation fill level. This is the amount of constraint matrix fill to allow in a single aggregation step.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.BarOrder
member.summary: Barrier ordering strategy. By default, the algorithm chooses automatically.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.Sifting
member.summary: Dual simplex sifting strategy for LP, MIP root and MIP nodes. By default, the algorithm chooses automatically.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.InfProofCuts
member.summary: Infeasibility proof cut generation. Overrides the Cuts parameter.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.ConcurrentJobs
member.summary: The number of concurrent jobs for the distributed concurrent optimizer. A value of 'n' causes the concurrent optimizer to create 'n' independent models, using different parameter settings for each. Each of these models is sent to a distributed worker machine for processing. Use the WorkerPool parameter to point to the Remote Services cluster that will provide the distributed workers. The optimization terminates when the first model solves.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.PSDCuts
member.summary: PSD cut generation. Overrides the Cuts parameter.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.LazyConstraints
member.summary: Indicates whether lazy constraints are enabled. Programs that add lazy constraints must set this parameter to 1.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.Crossover
member.summary: Type of crossover performed after barrier. By default, the algorithm choose automatically.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.StartNumber
member.summary: Selects the MIP start index.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.QCPDual
member.summary: Indicator to compute QCP duals.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.Cuts
member.summary: Global cut generation control.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.IISMethod
member.summary: The method used to compute an Irreducible Infeasible Subsystem. Method 0 is typically much faster, but method 1 can product a much smaller IIS. Method 2 ignores the bound constraints.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.TuneResults
member.summary: The number of tuning results. The tuning tool often finds multiple parameter sets that produce better results than the baseline settings. This parameter controls how many of these sets should be retained when tuning is complete.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.ScenarioNumber
member.summary: selects the scenario index of multi-scenario models.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.CutPasses
member.summary: Maximum number of cut passes performed during cut generation.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.PrePasses
member.summary: Presolve pass limit. Controls the number of passes performed by presolve. The default value of -1 chooses automatically.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.BarHomogeneous
member.summary: Determines whether the homogeneous algorithm is used when solving a model using barrier.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.VarBranch
member.summary: Branch variable selection strategy.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.CSBatchMode
member.summary: When set to 1, enable the local creation of models, and later submit batch-optimization jobs to the Cluster Manager. Note that if CSBatchMode is enabled, only batch-optimization calls are allowed. You must set this parameter through either a gurobi.lic file (using CSBATCHMODE=1) or an empty environment. Changing the parameter after your environment has been started will result in an error. Only for Gurobi Cluster Manager.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.DistributedMIPJobs
member.summary: Determines whether distributed MIP is used. A value of 'n' causes the MIP solver to divide the work of solving the MIP model among 'n' worker machines. Use the WorkerPool parameter to point to the Remote Services cluster that will provide the distributed workers.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.PreDepRow
member.summary: Determines whether presolve attempts to remove linearly dependent rows from the model. By default, the dependent row reduction is on for continuous models and off for MIP models.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.BranchDir
member.summary: Branch direction. Modify the order in which MIP nodes are explored in the branch-and-cut search. After processing a node, the default setting chooses the more promising child node to explore next. A setting of -1 will always explore the down branch first, while a setting of 1 will always explore the up branch first.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.PreQLinearize
member.summary: Controls presolve Q matrix linearization. Options 1 and 2 attempt to linearize quadratic constraints or a quadratic objective. Option 1 focuses on getting a strong LP relaxation. Option 2 aims for a compact relaxation. Option 0 always leaves Q matrices unmodified. The default setting (-1) chooses automatically.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.IgnoreNames
member.summary: Indicates whether to ignore names provided by users.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.TuneTrials
member.summary: The number of tuning trials. Performance on a MIP model can sometimes experience significant variations due to random effects. As a result, the tuning tool may return parameter sets that improve on the baseline only due to randomness. This parameter allows you to perform multiple solves for each parameter set, using different random number seeds for each, in order to reduce the influence of randomness on the results.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.NormAdjust
member.summary: The pricing norm variant. By default, the algorithm chooses automatically.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.PreCrush
member.summary: Shuts off a few reductions in order to allow presolve to transform any constraint on the original model into an equivalent constraint on the presolved model. You should consider setting this parameter to 1 if you are using callbacks to add your own cuts. A cut that cannot be applied to the presolved model will be silently ignored. The impact on the size of the presolved problem is usually small..

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.Disconnected
member.summary: Disconnected component strategy. A MIP model can sometimes be made up of multiple, completely independent sub-models. This parameter controls how aggressively we try to exploit this structure. A value of 0 ignores this structure entirely, while larger values try more aggressive approaches. The default value of -1 chooses automatically.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.BarCorrectors
member.summary: The number of central corrections applied during the barrier solution.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.CliqueCuts
member.summary: Clique cut generation. Overrides the Cuts parameter.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.MIPFocus
member.summary: Focus of MIP search. Allows you to change the focus to finding feasible solution, proving optimality, or moving the objective bound.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.FuncPieces
member.summary: Control PWL translation of general function constraints without own options specified, whether to use equal piece length, to limit error or to limit the total number of pieces.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.RLTCuts
member.summary: RLT cut generation. Overrides the Cuts parameter.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.ScaleFlag
member.summary: The model scaling.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.LogToConsole
member.summary: Indicates whether the Gurobi log should be sent to the console.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.MIPSepCuts
member.summary: MIP separation cut generation. Overrides the Cuts parameter.

member.summary: Maximum number of aggregation passes performed during cut generation. Overrides the Cuts parameter.

member.name: F:Gurobi.GRB.IntParam.CoverCuts
member.summary: Cover cut generation. Overrides the Cuts parameter.

member.summary: Controls how to deal with non-convex quadratic programs.

member.summary: Use insecure mode in TLS for Compute Server.

member.summary: Projected implied bound cut generation. Overrides the Cuts parameter.

member.summary: The cluster that will provide the distributed workers. member.summary: Gets or sets the feasrelax BigM for the cardinality type.

member.summary: Gets or sets the error allowed for PWL translation of general function constraints without own options specified.

member.name: P:Gurobi.GRBModel.EnvParameters.FuncMaxVal

member.name: P:Gurobi.GRBModel.EnvParameters.ImproveStartGap
member.summary: Gets or sets the optimality gap at which the MIP solve will switch to a strategy that gives up on moving the best bound and instead devotes all of its effort towards finding better feasible solutions.

member.name: P:Gurobi.GRBModel.EnvParameters.ImproveStartNodes
member.summary: Gets or sets the explored node count at which the MIP solve will switch to a strategy that gives up on moving the best bound and instead devotes all of its effort towards finding better feasible solutions.

member.name: P:Gurobi.GRBModel.EnvParameters.ImproveStartTime
member.summary: Gets or sets the elapsed solver runtime at which the MIP solve will switch to a strategy that gives up on moving the best bound and instead devotes all of its effort towards finding better feasible solutions.

member.name: P:Gurobi.GRBModel.EnvParameters.IntFeasTol
member.summary: Gets or sets the integer feasibility tolerance. Integer variables must take values that are no more than the specified tolerance away from the nearest integer.

member.name: P:Gurobi.GRBModel.EnvParameters.IterationLimit

member.name: P:Gurobi.GRBModel.EnvParameters.MIPGap

member.name: P:Gurobi.GRBModel.EnvParameters.MIPGapAbs

member.name: P:Gurobi.GRBModel.EnvParameters.MarkowitzTol

member.summary: Gets or sets the branch direction. Modify the order in which MIP nodes are explored in the branch-and-cut search. After processing a node, the default setting chooses the more promising child node to explore next. member.name: P:Gurobi.GRBModel.EnvParameters.ConcurrentJobs
member.summary: Gets or sets the number of concurrent jobs for the distributed concurrent optimizer. A value of 'n' causes the concurrent optimizer to create 'n' independent models, using different parameter settings for each. Each of these models is sent to a distributed worker machine for processing. Use the WorkerPool parameter to point to the Remote Services cluster that will provide the distributed workers. The optimization terminates when the first model solves.

member.name: P:Gurobi.GRBModel.EnvParameters.ConcurrentMIP
member.summary: Gets or sets the number of concurrent MIP jobs. A value of 'n' causes the MIP solver to solve 'n' independent MIP models, using different parameter settings for each. The optimization terminates when the the first model solves.

member.summary: Gets or sets the number of jobs for distributed parallel tuning. A value of 'n' causes the tuning tool to distribute tuning work among 'n' parallel jobs. member.name: P:Gurobi.GRBModel.EnvParameters.TuneOutput
member.summary: Gets or sets the amount of output produced by the tuning tool. Level 0 produces no output; level 1 produces tuning summary output only when a new best parameter set is found; level 2 produces tuning summary output for each parameter set that is tried; level 3 produces tuning summary output, plus detailed solver output, for each parameter set tried.

member.name: P:Gurobi.GRBModel.EnvParameters.TuneResults
member.summary: Gets or sets the number of tuning results. The tuning tool often finds multiple parameter sets that produce better results than the baseline settings. This parameter controls how many of these sets should be retained when tuning is complete.

member.name: P:Gurobi.GRBModel.EnvParameters.TuneTrials
member.summary: Gets or sets the number of tuning trials. Performance on a MIP model can sometimes experience significant variations due to random effects. As a result, the tuning tool may return parameter sets that improve on the baseline only due to randomness. This parameter allows you to perform multiple solves for each parameter set, using different random number seeds for each, in order to reduce the influence of randomness on the results.
